olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 bag baby broccoli
2 potato
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 tsp brown sugar
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Beetroot Relish
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Boil the kettle. Peel garlic. Trim baby broccoli. Cut potato into large chunks.
Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water over high heat with a pinch
of salt.
• Cook potato and garlic in boiling water for 10 minutes. Place a colander or
steamer basket on top of the saucepan, then add baby broccoli. Cover with
a lid and steam until broccoli is tender and potato can be easily pierced with
a fork, 5 minutes.
• Transfer baby broccoli to a medium bowl and season to taste. Set aside.
Drain potato and garlic, then return to saucepan.
• Add chicken-style stock powder, the milk and the butter to the saucepan,
then mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, combine Aussie spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of
salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Add pork loin steaks and turn to coat.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, cook pork until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.
• Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of
olive oil.
• Cook shredded cabbage mix until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add the brown sugar, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and a splash of water
and cook until softened, 3-4 minutes.

• Slice pork steaks.
• Divide garlic mash, pork, sautéed cabbage and steamed baby broccoli
between plates.
• Top pork with beetroot relish to serve.